Let $M$ be the midpoint of $AB$, so $AM=BM=1$. Since $\triangle ABG$ is equilateral, we have $AG=BG=AB=2$. Since $G$ is the centroid, we have $GM=\frac{1}{3}AM=\frac{1}{3}$ and $GC=2GM=\frac{2}{3}$. 

[asy]
pair A,B,C,G,M;
A=(0,0);
B=(2,0);
C=(1,2);
G=(1,0.666);
M=(1,0);
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(G--A);
draw(G--B);
draw(G--C);
draw(M--G);
label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,N);
label("$G$",G,S);
label("$M$",M,N);
[/asy]

Since $G$ is the centroid, we have $CG=2GM$ and $AG=2BG$, so $AC=2AG=4$ and $BC=2BG=4$. Therefore, the perimeter of $\triangle ABC$ is $AB+BC+CA=2+4+4=\boxed{10}$.

