\[b^2 = a^2 + a^2 - 2a^2 \cos \angle PQR = 2a^2 - 2a^2 \cos \angle PQR.\]Since $\cos \angle PQM = -\cos \angle PQR$, the Law of Cosines on triangle $PQM$ gives us
\[a^2 = QM^2 + b^2 - 2 \cdot QM \cdot b \cdot \cos \angle PQM.\]Then $QM \cdot b = 17 \cdot 32$, so
