By the Angle Bisector Theorem,
\[\frac{BD}{DC} = \frac{AB}{AC} = \frac{3}{5}.\]Let $BD = 3x$ and $DC = 5x.$  Then $BC = 8x,$ so $x = \frac{1}{2}.$  Hence, $BD = \frac{3}{2}$ and $DC = \frac{5}{2}.$

