The area of each rectangle is the product of its adjacent side lengths, so the total area of the rectangles is $1\cdot 2 + 2\cdot 4 + 1\cdot 2 + 2\cdot 4 = 18.$

The square has side length 2, so its area is $2^2 = 4.$

Therefore, the total area of the octagon is $18 + 4 = \boxed{22}.$

