llm_step:
Since $AC = AB,$ triangle $ABC$ is isosceles, so $\angle BCA = \angle BAC = 42^\circ.$  Then $\angle ACD = \angle BCD - \angle BCA.$  Since $ED$ is tangent to the circle at $C,$ $\angle CED = \angle BCA = 42^\circ.$

